Here is a brief example of how the decimal data type can be used in OpenROAD Actian 4GL programming language to store and operate with currency amounts. For example:

decimal(6,2) column_name;
This declares the column_name as a decimal value with six digits before the decimal point (precision), two digits after the decimal point (scale). To store $50 in this field, you would enter 50.00, and to retrieve it back, you could use `cast(column_name as varchar(7))` which will produce a string containing $50.00.
